message: Focus on combining ingredients that share the *same physical state* (e.g., liquid with liquid, solid with solid, gas with gas) but have *different magical properties* (one magical, one mundane). My best result was combining 'honey nectar' (liquid, mundane) with 'kraken ink' (liquid, magical) for a value of 40. To get 60 points, create two 30-value items: one from a 'mundane' source (e.g., filtered morning dew) and one from a 'magical' source (e.g., filtered ghostly vapor). Next, use the 'vial' tool on *each* of these two 30-value items (they will become 10-value). Finally, combine the 10-value 'mundane' item with the 10-value 'magical' item to achieve 60 points. Avoid 'solid' ingredients with the 'filter' tool as they typically yield negative results. Combining two 10-value 'magical' items gives only 20 points.

Use a 'vial' on a 'solid, magical' ingredient (like unicorn horn or mandrake root) to get a 30-value 'liquid, extracted, magical' item. Then, use a 'vial' on a 'solid, mundane' ingredient (like dandelion or amber) to get a 30-value 'liquid, extracted, mundane' item. Combining these two specific 30-value items (one magical, one mundane) yields 100 points. Avoid using the 'vial' on 'gas' or 'liquid' ingredients, as this results in negative 'botched extraction' items. The 'filter' tool also seems to worsen negative items, and combining raw ingredients yields negative values.

message: The previous player's hint about combining two '30s' (after using a vial on each) did not work for me; I never found 30-value items, and combining two vialed items (even positive ones) led to negative values. The most successful strategy I found was to combine two raw ingredients to get an item with a value of -60, then use the 'vial' tool on *that specific -60 item*. This consistently turned it into a +50 value item. The 'filter' tool generally made items worse. Avoid combining items that have already been processed with tools. Focus on finding which initial raw ingredient combinations result in a -60 value, then vial them.
